# Deed of Trust and Security Agreement

Draft a dual-collateral security instrument that secures a loan with real property and UCC personal property.

## Prerequisites

1. **Parties** — full legal names, entity types, jurisdictions, addresses, and signer authority for Grantor/Borrower (Debtor), Trustee, and Beneficiary/Lender (Secured Party).
2. **Secured obligations** — principal, interest, payment schedule, maturity, default rate, fees, future advances, cross-default scope, and related guarantees.
3. **Real property** — legal description, street address, APN, title exceptions, easements, leases, fixtures, and improvements.
4. **Personal property collateral** — collateral categories, item schedules, serial numbers, locations, IP, accounts, and proceeds.
5. **Jurisdictional rules** — state deed of trust statute, recording requirements, trustee sale notice/cure, deficiency/redemption limits, homestead or spousal joinder rules.
6. **Insurance/taxes/environment** — coverages, loss payee requirements, escrow terms, and any environmental reports.
7. **Related documents** — note, loan agreement, assignment of leases/rents, intercreditor/subordination agreements.

## Output Structure / Process

**Data Intake Table**

| Item | Required details | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Parties | Names, entity type, address, authority | Match public records for debtor name |
| Secured obligations | Note/loan agreement references | Include future advances if intended |
| Real property | Legal description, APN, address | Attach as Exhibit A |
| Fixtures | List or define by category | Tie to real property collateral |
| Personal property | UCC categories, schedules, locations | Attach as Exhibit B |
| Notices | Addresses, methods, timing | Align with loan agreement |
| Governing law | Situs state + UCC debtor location | Separate if different |

**Document Outline (Required Sections)**

1. Parties and defined terms.
2. Recitals linking to the note/loan agreement.
3. Grant of Deed of Trust with power of sale and defeasance.
4. Security Agreement grant for personal property collateral.
5. Fixture filing provisions and as-extracted collateral (if applicable).
6. Assignment of leases and rents (if applicable).
7. Representations and warranties.
8. Covenants: payment, taxes, insurance, maintenance, compliance, preservation.
9. Events of Default with notice/cure.
10. Remedies: trustee sale process and UCC Article 9 remedies.
11. Notices, governing law, choice-of-law, integration, amendments.
12. Substitution of trustee and trustee protections.
13. Receivership and protective advances.
14. Execution, acknowledgments, and recording instructions.

**Collateral Description Rules**

- Use the real property legal description verbatim; attach as Exhibit A.
- Define fixtures and improvements as part of the real property collateral.
- For UCC collateral, list categories and include proceeds; specify equipment and inventory locations.
- Include deposit accounts or investment property only if control agreements are required or planned.
- State whether after-acquired property is included.

**Default/Remedy Matrix**

| Default type | Notice/cure | Remedies |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Payment default | Exact grace period | Acceleration; trustee sale |
| Covenant breach | Reasonable cure period | Acceleration; protective advances |
| Bankruptcy/insolvency | Typically no cure | Stay relief; receiver |
| Unauthorized transfer/encumbrance | Immediate or short cure | Acceleration; injunctive relief |
| Insurance/tax failure | Short cure; lender may pay | Add to secured debt |

**Execution/Recording Checklist**

- Confirm trustee eligibility under state law.
- Confirm notarization and witness requirements.
- Obtain spousal or owner joinder if required by homestead/community property rules.
- Provide recording instructions and return address.
- Prepare UCC-1 financing statement with exact debtor name and address.
- Cross-check defined terms with the note/loan agreement.

**Template Skeleton**

```text
DEED OF TRUST AND SECURITY AGREEMENT

This Agreement is made as of [Date] between [Grantor], [Trustee], and [Beneficiary].

1. Recitals
1.1 Secured Obligations. [Describe note/loan agreement and any future advances.]

2. Grant of Deed of Trust
[Conveyance language; power of sale; defeasance on payment.]

3. Security Agreement
[Grant of security interest in Personal Property; proceeds; after-acquired.]

4. Representations and Warranties
[...]

5. Covenants
[...]

6. Events of Default
[...]

7. Remedies
[Trustee sale process; UCC Article 9 remedies; application of proceeds.]

8. Miscellaneous
[Notices; governing law; amendments; successors/assigns.]

Signatures and Acknowledgments
[Notary blocks; entity authority.]

Exhibit A - Legal Description
Exhibit B - Personal Property Collateral Schedule
```

## Guidelines

- Separate governing law for real property (situs) and UCC collateral (debtor location); state both if different.
- Match debtor name to public organizational records to avoid UCC filing defects.
- Do not paraphrase the legal description; use the title report text verbatim.
- Use exact statutory notice and cure periods; do not insert generic timing.
- Verify whether the deed of trust serves as a fixture filing in the jurisdiction.
- If waiving redemption, deficiency, homestead, or jury trial rights, confirm enforceability and required language [VERIFY].
- Ensure remedy sequencing aligns with the note and any intercreditor or subordination terms.
- Keep cross-references consistent and define "Secured Obligations" precisely.
